Pre-Game Insights: The Eswatini Senior Men’s national team (Sihlangu SeMnikati) assistant coach, Sifiso Ntibane, and Mali Head Coach Tom Saintfiet predict a tough match when the two national teams play on Tuesday, 10th September 2024 at the Mbombela Stadium in the TotalEnergies AFCON Qualifiers.
Sifiso Ntibane highlighted that Mali has good players who play in big leagues, which testifies to their quality.
Ntibane mentioned that Eswatini players are motivated to play against Mali, one of the big football nations in Africa.
Ntibane expressed concern about Eswatini's recent lack of goal conversion despite creating many scoring opportunities.
Tom Saintfiet acknowledged that Eswatini is a good team, having only suffered narrow defeats against Guinea Bissau and Angola in recent matches.
Saintfiet noted that Eswatini has good players like Justice Figueredo, who plays in the Betway Premiership in South Africa.
